SMS
Last updated December 23rd, 2025

Overview
The Hubtel SMS API allows businesses to integrate SMS functionality into their applications. With this API, you can send:

Send Simple/Batch Messages to individuals or groups of people (batch).
Send Personalized Messages to individuals or groups of people (batch).
Hubtel also provides an SMPP (Short Message Peer-to-Peer) route for sending SMS, which allows high-throughput message delivery suitable for large-scale applications.

The reference provides an overview of the Hubtel SMS API endpoints for interacting programmatically within your application and a guide to help you integrate with Hubtel's SMS SMPP route effectively.


SMPP
The SMPP route is designed for enterprises requiring reliable and efficient SMS delivery. It supports standard SMPP protocol features and ensures availability and scalability.

SMPP Connection
To connect to Hubtel's SMPP server, use the following details:

Host: smpp.hubtel.com
Port: 2775
ClientID
ClientSecret
bulb-icon
Note
Contact your Retail Systems Engineer for your ClientID and ClientSecret.

Supported Operations
Hubtel's SMPP route supports the following operations:

Bind Transmitter (TX): To send SMS messages.
Bind Receiver (RX): To receive delivery receipts.
Bind Transceiver (TRX): To send and receive messages and receipts.
Submit_SM: To submit a single SMS message.
Deliver_SM: To receive delivery receipts.
Unbind: To close the SMPP session.
Please refer to the detailed SMPP documentation provided here for further understanding.


SMS API
The Hubtel SMS API allows you to integrate multiple SMS functionalities into your applications. This document focuses on:

Simple Messaging: send messages to individuals using POST and GET.
Batch Simple Messaging: send simple messages to a group of people.
Batch Personalized Messaging: Send personalized messages to a group of people.
Message Status Check: Check the status of a message with messageId or batchId.

API Reference

Simple SEND SMS GET
This endpoint allows you to send a simple message using GET method. You will need to pass clientId and clientSecret in the request.

API Endpoint	https://sms.hubtel.com/v1/messages/send?clientsecret=xxxxxxxx&clientid=xxxxxxxx&from=Hubtel&to=0244xxxxxx&content=Helloworld
Request Type	GET

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
clientid	String	Mandatory	ClientId needed to authenticate SMS request. You can find your clientid here.
clientsecret	String	Mandatory	Clientsecret needed to authenticate SMS request. You can find your clientsecret here.
from	String	Mandatory	Sender ID or Name recipients will see. Maximum characters for this value is 11.
to	String	Mandatory	Mobile number of recipient.
content	String	Mandatory	Content of the simple message

SAMPLE REQUEST
HTTP

copy
Copy
  GET /v1/messages/send?clientsecret=sgrorne&clientid=qoohqvcp&from=Abrantie&to=233546335113&content="GoTesting" HTTP/1.1
  Host: sms.hubtel.com

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
rate	Float	Cost per sms
messageId	String	Unique identifier of messages
status	Int	Status code of the requeest
networkId	String	networkId of message
clientReference	String	ClientReference of message. Can be null
statusDescription	String	Brief description of request status

SAMPLE RESPONSE
201 Created

copy
Copy
  {
      "rate": 0.0309,
      "messageId": "9c5f3edc-529e-4182-959b-aeb17b9ddad4", 
      "status": 0,
      "networkId": "62001", 
      "clientReference": null,
      "statusDescription": "request submitted successfully"
  }

Simple SEND SMS POST
This endpoint allows you to send a simple message using POST method. Send an HTTP POST request to the below URL and authenticate your request with Basic Auth using your SMS API credentials.

API Endpoint	https://sms.hubtel.com/v1/messages/send
Request Type	POST
Content Type	JSON

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
From	String	Mandatory	SenderId or Name recipients will see. Maximum characters for this value is 11.
To	String	Mandatory	Mobile number of recipient.
Content	String	Mandatory	Content of the message.

SAMPLE REQUEST
HTTP

copy
Copy
  POST /v1/messages/send HTTP/1.1 
  Host: sms.hubtel.com
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Basic cW92Y7c2dyb3Juam=
  {
    "From": "AbrantieLai",
    "To": "233546335113",
    "Content": "This is a test. Kindly ignore."
  }

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
rate	Float	Cost per sms
messageId	String	Unique identifier of messages
status	Int	Status code of the requeest
networkId	String	networkId of message
clientReference	String	ClientReference of message. Can be null
statusDescription	String	Brief description of request status

SAMPLE RESPONSE
201 Created

copy
Copy
{
  "rate": 0.0246,
  "messageId": "fab43849-6c5b-4334-a88b-d06520b1ace8",
  "status": 0,
  "networkId": "62002",
  "clientReference": null,
  "statusDescription": "request submitted successfully"
}

Batch Simple Messaging
This endpoint allows you to send messages to a group of people. Send an HTTP POST request to the below URL and authenticate your request with Basic Auth using your SMS API credentials.

API Endpoint	https://sms.hubtel.com/v1/messages/batch/simple/send
Request Type	POST
Content Type	JSON

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
From	String	Mandatory	SenderId or Name recipients will see. Maximum characters for this value is 11.
Recipients	Array	Mandatory	MSISDNs to receive of message
Content	String	Mandatory	Content of the simple message

SAMPLE REQUEST
HTTP

copy
Copy
  POST /v1/messages/batch/simple/send HTTP/1.1 
  Host: sms.hubtel.com
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Basic cW92Y6c2dyb3Juam=
  {
      "From": "AbrantieLai",
      "Recipients": [
          "233546335113",
          "233501431586"
      ],
      "Content": "Welcome to the first ever bulk SMS via API in Ghana"
  }

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
batchId	String	The ID of the batch of messages
status	Int	Status code of the request returned by SMS API
data	ArrayOfObjects	This contains other objects
recipient	String	MSISDNs to receive message
content	String	Content of the simple message
messageId	String	Unique identifier of message

SAMPLE RESPONSE
200 OK

copy
Copy
{
  "batchId": "165949ee-431b-4bf8-9eca-108058a8bc32", 
  "status": 0,
  "data": [
    {
      "recipient": "233546335113",
      "content": "Welcome to the first ever bulk SMS via API in Ghana", 
      "messageId": "e80133f9-e822-457c-98fb-d217bc4a1f83"
    }, 
    {
      "recipient": "233501431586",
      "content": "Welcome to the first ever bulk SMS via API in Ghana", 
      "messageId": "ebc7948a-7c81-4396-9104-9c99fc921069"
    } 
  ]
}

Batch Personalized Messaging
This endpoint allows you to send personalized messages to a group of people. Send an HTTP POST request to the below URL and authenticate your request with Basic Authentication using your SMS API credentials.

API Endpoint	https://sms.hubtel.com/v1/messages/batch/personalized/send
Request Type	POST
Content Type	JSON
REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
From	String	Mandatory	SenderId or Name recipients will see. Maximum characters for this value is 11.
personalizedRecipients	ArrayOfObjects	Mandatory	Contains object of recipients and content.
To	String	Mandatory	MSISDNs to receive message
Content	String	Mandatory	Content of the simple message

SAMPLE REQUEST
HTTP

copy
Copy
  POST /v1/messages/batch/personalized/send HTTP/1.1 
  Host: sms.hubtel.com
  Content-Type: application/json
  Authorization: Basic cW92Y6c2dyb3Juam=

  {
      "From" : "AbrantieCo",
      "personalizedRecipients": [
        {
            "To": "233501431586",
            "Content":"Hi Pheezy, thank you for all you do for this business"
        },
        {
            "To": "233501431586",
            "Content":"Hi Joe, thank you for all you do for this business"
        }
      ],
  }

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
batchId	String	The ID of the batch of messages
status	Int	Status code of the request returned by SMS API
data	ArrayOfObjects	This contains other objects
recipient	String	MSISDNs to receive message
content	String	Content of the simple message
messageId	String	Unique identifier of message

SAMPLE RESPONSE
200 OK

copy
Copy
{
    "batchId": "18ee6a2a-29ac-41c6-b70f-de809b040584", 
    "status": 0,
    "data": [ 
      {
          "recipient": "233501431586",
          "content": "Hi Pheezy, thank you for all you do for this business", 
          "messageId": "350fd34d-dce1-4694-a4c9-d9b97d1f4593"
      }, 
      {
          "recipient": "233546335113",
          "content": "Hi Joe, thank you for all you do for this business", 
          "messageId": "f58e7f2a-203a-4079-a518-7f6647099b5e"
      }
    ]
}

Status Check
This helps to check for the status of an SMS by providing an identifier.


Status Check with MessageID
A query to this endpoint returns the status of a single message.

bulb-icon
Note
Replace the messageID in the below endpoint with the messageID of your messages.

API Endpoint	https://sms.hubtel.com/v1/messages/{messageId}
Request Type	GET

REQUEST PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Requirement	Description
messageID	String	Mandatory	An ID of one of the sent messages

SAMPLE REQUEST (Message ID)
HTTP

copy
Copy
  GET /v1/messages/batch/ eadbfcd0-94d1-438f-ad32-0013f34042c2 HTTP/1.1 
  Host: sms.hubtel.com

RESPONSE PARAMETERS
Parameter	Type	Description
rate	Float	Cost per sms
batchId	String	Unique identifier of batch message.
messageId	String	Unique identifier of individual message.
content	String	Content of the simple message.
status	String	Current status of message based on DeliveryReceipt (DLR) by Telco.
updateTime	String	DLR update time.
time	String	The time SMS was sent.
to	String	MSISDN to receive message.
from	String	SenderId or name recipient will see.

SAMPLE RESPONSE
200 OK

copy
Copy
{
  "rate": 0.0309,
  "batchId": null,
  "messageId": "eadbfcd0-94d1-438f-ad32-0013f34042c2",
  "content": "The Job is the JOB","status": "Delivered",
  "status": "Delivered",
  "updateTime": "2023-05-30T16:43:15",
  "time": "2023-05-30T16:43:13.7208383Z",
  "to": "233546335113",
  "from": "AbrantieCo"
}

